Make guardrails portable across AI assistants

Restructure so the same guidance works with Cursor, Claude Code, claude.ai,
GitHub Copilot Chat, OpenAI Codex CLI (and other AGENTS.md-compatible tools),
ChatGPT, Gemini, and Mistral Le Chat.

Adds:

- PROMPT.md — canonical paste-ready system prompt with delimited section,
  the single source of truth for review rules
- AGENTS.md — entry point for OpenAI Codex CLI, Aider, Continue, Cline,
  Cody, Amp, and other tools that follow the AGENTS.md convention
- .github/copilot-instructions.md — entry point for GitHub Copilot Chat
- .cursor/rules/hipaa-terraform-aws.mdc — Cursor Project Rule that auto-
  attaches when editing *.tf / *.tfvars / *.hcl
- docs/usage/{chatgpt,claude,gemini,mistral}.md — per-tool quickstarts for
  Custom GPTs, Claude.ai Projects, Gemini Gems, and Le Chat Agents

Updates:

- README.md — compatibility matrix, per-tool quickstarts, repository
  layout, data-handling note for consumer AI tools
- CLAUDE.md — now covers both Claude Code and claude.ai Projects, points
  at PROMPT.md as the canonical source
- .cursor/skills/hipaa-terraform-aws/SKILL.md — cross-references PROMPT.md
  for cross-tool reuse
